<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="399" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,429,1145]" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis box="[199,315,498,521]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,498,521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Distinguished from all extant species of 
<taxonomicName box="[773,857,498,521]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[773,857,498,521]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">Spizella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[874,986,498,521]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Passerella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[874,986,498,521]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">Passerella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wagler" authorityYear="1831" box="[1002,1066,498,521]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Junco" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1002,1066,498,521]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">Junco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[1130,1256,498,521]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Zonotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1130,1256,498,521]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">Zonotrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by (1) a yellow lower mandible contrasting with a black upper mandible and (2) strongly divergent molecular characters (
<bibRefCitation author="Klicka, J. &amp; Barker, F. K. &amp; Burns, K. J. &amp; Lanyon, S. M. &amp; Lovette, I. J. &amp; Chaves, J. A. &amp; Bryson, R. W. Jr." pageId="1" pageNumber="399" pagination="177 - 182" refId="ref1917" refString="Klicka, J., Barker, F. K., Burns, K. J., Lanyon, S. M., Lovette, I. J., Chaves, J. A. &amp; Bryson, R. W. Jr. (2014) A comprehensive multilocus assessment of sparrow (Family Passerellidae) relationships. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 77, 177 - 182. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2014.04.025" type="journal article" year="2014">
Klicka 
<emphasis box="[1381,1436,533,556]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). Further distinguished from the six species of 
<emphasis box="[780,891,568,591]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">
<taxonomicName box="[780,864,568,591]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Spizella</taxonomicName>
—
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Cabanis)" baseAuthorityName="Cabanis" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[891,1132,568,591]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atrogularis">
<emphasis box="[891,1010,568,591]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">atrogularis</emphasis>
(Cabanis)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Cassin)" baseAuthorityName="Cassin" box="[1152,1341,568,591]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="breweri">
<emphasis box="[1152,1234,568,591]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">breweri</emphasis>
(Cassin)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Swainson)" baseAuthorityName="Swainson" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis box="[1360,1435,568,591]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">pallida</emphasis>
(Swainson)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bechstein)" baseAuthorityName="Bechstein" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[291,532,602,625]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="passerina">
<emphasis box="[291,395,602,625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">passerina</emphasis>
(Bechstein)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wilson)" baseAuthorityName="Wilson" box="[548,729,602,625]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis box="[548,621,602,625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">pusilla</emphasis>
(Wilson)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ridgway)" baseAuthorityName="Ridgway" box="[796,1014,602,625]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wortheni">
<emphasis box="[796,891,602,625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">wortheni</emphasis>
(Ridgway)
</taxonomicName>
—by (1) distinctive plumage features including rufous crown, rufous postocular stripe, and pale gray underparts with a dark central breast spot; (2) larger size on average (wing chord 
<quantity box="[411,529,672,695]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.45" metricValueMax="8.2" metricValueMin="6.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" unit="mm" value="74.5" valueMax="82.0" valueMin="67.0">67–82 mm</quantity>
, tail 
<quantity box="[581,700,672,695]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" metricValueMax="7.4" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" unit="mm" value="67.0" valueMax="74.0" valueMin="60.0">60–74 mm</quantity>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pyle, P." box="[710,822,672,695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" refId="ref2197" refString="Pyle, P. (1997) Identification guide to North American birds, Part I. Slate Creek Press, Bolinas, California, 732 pp." type="book" year="1997">Pyle 1997</bibRefCitation>
); and (3) lateroventral process (LP) of the laterosphenoid 0.8–1.3 times the length of the zygomatic process (ZP) and with a wide, flat tip (vs. LP short (0.1–0.4 times the length of the ZP) in five species of 
<taxonomicName box="[422,506,741,764]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[422,506,741,764]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">Spizella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName box="[521,642,741,764]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wortheni">
<emphasis box="[521,642,741,764]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">S. wortheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
not examined; 
<bibRefCitation author="Patten, M. A. &amp; Fugate, M." box="[806,1043,741,764]" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" pagination="412 - 424" refId="ref2118" refString="Patten, M. A. &amp; Fugate, M. (1998) Systematic relationships among the emberizid sparrows. The Auk, 115, 412 - 424. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 4089200" type="journal article" year="1998">Patten &amp; Fugate 1998</bibRefCitation>
). Further told from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Merrem" baseAuthorityYear="1786" box="[1251,1430,741,764]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Passerella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="iliaca">
<emphasis box="[1251,1430,741,764]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">Passerella iliaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, its sister taxon according to the most complete molecular phylogeny (
<bibRefCitation author="Klicka, J. &amp; Barker, F. K. &amp; Burns, K. J. &amp; Lanyon, S. M. &amp; Lovette, I. J. &amp; Chaves, J. A. &amp; Bryson, R. W. Jr." box="[943,1156,776,799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" pagination="177 - 182" refId="ref1917" refString="Klicka, J., Barker, F. K., Burns, K. J., Lanyon, S. M., Lovette, I. J., Chaves, J. A. &amp; Bryson, R. W. Jr. (2014) A comprehensive multilocus assessment of sparrow (Family Passerellidae) relationships. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 77, 177 - 182. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2014.04.025" type="journal article" year="2014">
Klicka 
<emphasis box="[1028,1087,776,799]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
), by plumage characters, including a conspicuous lack of dense, dark streaking or spotting on the underparts. Separated from all extant species of 
<emphasis box="[151,303,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">
<taxonomicName box="[151,276,845,868]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Zonotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Zonotrichia</taxonomicName>
—
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Gmelin)" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" box="[303,531,845,868]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Zonotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atricapilla">
<emphasis box="[303,412,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">atricapilla</emphasis>
(Gmelin)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gmelin)" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" box="[559,777,845,868]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Zonotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albicollis">
<emphasis box="[559,658,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">albicollis</emphasis>
(Gmelin)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Muller)" baseAuthorityName="Muller" box="[804,1007,845,868]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Zonotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis box="[804,896,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">capensis</emphasis>
(Müller)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Forster)" baseAuthorityName="Forster" box="[1035,1268,845,868]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Zonotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucophrys">
<emphasis box="[1035,1152,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">leucophrys</emphasis>
(Forster)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nuttall)" baseAuthorityName="Nuttall" baseAuthorityYear="1840" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Zonotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="querula">
<emphasis box="[1353,1436,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">querula</emphasis>
(Nuttall)
</taxonomicName>
—and 
<emphasis box="[315,500,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wagler" authorityYear="1831" box="[315,379,880,903]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Junco" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Junco</taxonomicName>
— 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[405,500,880,903]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Junco" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hyemalis">hyemalis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wagler)" baseAuthorityName="Wagler" box="[514,740,880,903]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Junco" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="phaeonotus">
<emphasis box="[514,637,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">phaeonotus</emphasis>
(Wagler)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Boucard)" baseAuthorityName="Boucard" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[797,990,880,903]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Junco" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vulcani">
<emphasis box="[797,875,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">vulcani</emphasis>
(Boucard)
</taxonomicName>
—species by rufous crown and, in adults, a combination of dark iris and dorsal plumage streaking.
</paragraph>
