<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="399" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,429,1145]" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1018,1041]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Slager &amp; Klicka" authorityYear="2014" box="[548,675,1018,1041]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizelloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[548,675,1018,1041]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">Spizelloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is formed from the sparrow genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1052,1137,1018,1041]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1052,1137,1018,1041]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">Spizella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the Greek suffix 
<emphasis box="[1371,1435,1018,1041]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">-oidēs</emphasis>
(resembling; 
<bibRefCitation author="Brown, R. W." box="[294,433,1053,1076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" refId="ref1648" refString="Brown, R. W. (1956) Composition of Scientific Words. Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, DC, 882 pp." type="book" year="1956">Brown 1956</bibRefCitation>
). The name alludes to the evolutionary convergence in plumage, morphology, and behavior that led to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Slager &amp; Klicka" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Slager &amp; Klicka" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[277,500,1088,1111]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizelloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arborea">
<emphasis box="[277,500,1088,1111]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">Spizelloides arborea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being considered a 
<taxonomicName box="[732,816,1088,1111]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[732,816,1088,1111]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">Spizella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sparrow for many years. The gender of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Slager &amp; Klicka" authorityYear="2014" box="[1280,1407,1088,1111]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Spizelloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="399" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1280,1407,1088,1111]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="399">Spizelloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is feminine.
</paragraph>
